title: 820-4924-A .520A not turning on
message:
I have another macbook pro A1502 board model 820-4924-A that is consuming 520 ma, it does not have USB activity, it does not have thunderbolt activity. I have all the rails present (from the schematic page 68)... this is the second board that I have with this problem, please help me figure it out. 
The board is in S0 state, has cpu vcore, allsys_pwrgd
What else can I check? Thank you!

title: 820-4924-A .520A not turning on
message:
Any history available?
Check PLT_RESET_L and all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors.
You can also try to flash new BIOS.

title: 820-4924-A .520A not turning on
message:
Any history available? Left it on and the next morning won´t turn on...
Check PLT_RESET_L = 3.3v
SPI Bus Series Termination resistors = all with the correct values...

Thank you!
